snippet.title: Saving Voyager 1! - Bruce Waggoner at !!Con 2024
snippet.description:
Saving Voyager 1!

Both of the 47 year old Voyager spacecraft are currently in interstellar space and returning their most important data set; in-situ measurements of the magnetic field, plasma and dust beyond the Heliopause. In late 2023, Voyager 1 lost all downlink telemetry and the flight team had essentially no visibility into the state of the spacecraft which is over 15 billion miles from the Earth. This talk will detail how the flight team diagnosed the problem, and formulated a recovery plan to patch the Flight Data System flight software.

Bruce Waggoner is the Mission Assurance Manager at NASA Jet Propulsion Lab/Caltech. He graduated from the University of Nebraska with a BS in Physics and Astronomy. He has worked at JPL for 39 years supporting dozens of Earth orbiting and deep space missions. He also volunteers as a gymnastics coach and assists teaching girls engineering and science at a local high school.

Presented at !!Con 2024 (pronounced, of course, "bangbangcon"!) in Santa Cruz, CA -- https://bangbangcon.com/ 

!!Con is a production of the Exclamation Foundation -- https://exclamation.foundation/

snippet.title: SlugLoop Product Demo | Real-Time UCSC Bus Tracking
snippet.description:
Top 10 Finalist @ GDSC 2023 Global 

In this video, we're introducing SlugLoop, a real-time bus tracking app designed to streamline campus transportation at UC Santa Cruz. By displaying live locations of loop buses, SlugLoop enables students to make more informed travel decisions and reduces pressure on local metro buses.

SlugLoop’s goal is to provide students with accurate, up-to-date information on bus locations, helping them avoid long wait times and minimize congestion on metro buses. Built with an intuitive interface, SlugLoop is a practical solution to improve campus mobility.

Core Features:
- Real-time map of UCSC loop bus locations
- React-based UI for seamless mobile access
- Firebase integration for real-time data storage
- ExpressJS backend processing GPS data from loop buses
- Designed for scalability and community maintenance

Check out the project here! https://devpost.com/software/slugloop  
And the source code here! https://github.com/IdkwhatImD0ing/SlugLoop

-------------

snippet.title: How to Recreate "Schotter" (1960) Using P5JS
snippet.description:
In this video tutorial I will explain how you can recreate Schotter in P5JS and how you can make it your own. Schotter was created by George Nees in the 1960's and is one of the earliest examples of procedural art. If you follow this tutorial be sure to give it your own spin!

snippet.title: "Hotness"  ᵐᵃˡᵉ ᵛᵉʳ
snippet.description:
Seja bem vindo, esse é o começo de uma nova era acompanhada com novas tecnologias estudadas, faça bom proveito do áudio e sinta-se acolhido ❤

    Dês de já, me perdoeem, mudei a estética denovokkkkkk



 ¬ Esse áudio não vai te tornar literalmente uma "gostosura", e sim no sentido figurado. Então não se preocupemkkk.



Características no comentário fixado 📌




··································································
 · Ouça APENAS 3 vezes (sério, acabei desrespeitando o limite de escutas pra ver se o áudio estava funcionando e fiquei com um baita dor de cabeça).

 · Beba água antes e depois (210ml).

 · Pode ouvir como quiser, mas recomendo que use fones para que a tecnologia aplicada no áudio tenha efeito completo.

 · Não me responsabilizo pelos efeitos colaterais se desrespeitar o limite de escutas.
··································································
